article.headline: N. Colorado 88, E. Washington 80
article.story: CHENEY, Wash. -- Derrick Barden and Tevin Svihovec each scored 5 points in overtime to pace Northern Colorado to an 88-80 victory over Eastern Washington on Thursday night. Barden had a big all-around night for Northern Colorado (10-17, 8-10 Big Sky). He also grabbed 10 rebounds and came up with four steals. Three of his baskets were 3-pointers. Tate Unruh scored 21 points and handed out five assists and Svihovec finished with 16 points. Tyler Harvey scored 22 points to lead Eastern Washington (9-19, 6-11). Venky Jois scored 14 points, Martin Seiferth had 11 points and 21 rebounds and Parker Kelly had 10 points.
